features: 【8-TIER VERTICAL SHOE RACK】The 8 tier open shoe storage enable easy access and visibility for your shoes, keep your room neat and organized without occupying too much floor space. Put a pair of shoes per layer, helping to classify different types of shoes in daily needs.

【SPACE SAVING SHOE ORGANIZER】 Without occupying too much space, the dimension 10.2"D x 11"W x 48.3"H (28 x 26 x 123 cm) makes this shoe organizer an ideal storage solution for any narrow or tiny space, such as the closet, entryway, dormitory, bedroom, hallway, etc.

【MULTI-FUNCTIONAL STORAGE SHELF】 Functions as a shoe rack to provide storage space for shoes, boots, high heels, and sneakers. Performing well as a storage shelf or display rack to hold daily items, such as CDs, books, photo albums, plants, towels, small appliances, and more.

【STURDY WOODEN SHOE SHELF】Made of E1-grade MDF board and solid beech wood, this shoe shelf is much durable and sturdier to hold shoes and heavier item. Different from the rigid metal shoe racks and the fragile plastic shoe racks, this one is specially designed with a look of wood accent to be decorative enough to suit any corner of your house.

【Fit for varying shoe height】The bottom two layers are 7.9" high, which is perfect for high heels. Removing one board you will get a 15.7" space for your high boots. The top 5 layers are 5.9" high, making it well to hold flat shoes, slippers, sneakers, etc.
【No-Tool Assembly】Just twist the wood rods on according to the instructions，you can finish it in 3 minutes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is well made and was easy to put together. I needed a small shoe rack to get rid of the shoe clutter at my kitchen door. Shoes and ankle boots fit perfectly! It looks nice!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect shoe rack for an apartment.
reviews.reviewText: At first I was afraid some of the cubies would be too short for my sneakers (I only use this for sneakers), but they were the perfect size. The dowels that hold the tiers are thick and sturdy and the entire unit is easy to assemble. It looks nice and my very active cat has yet to be able to knock it over. My only criticism is that I wish they made one with two tiers so I could fit all the shoes. Buy a couple.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Must buy space saving shoe rack!!!
reviews.reviewText: Wow this is game changer! I wanted to store shoes but not have it take up our entry way and holy Toledo this is amazing. It fits my husbands size 13 shoes and I can fit several pairs of my toddlers shoes in one slot. It was super easy to put together as I watched my toddler all by myself. It is sturdy and looks good. My parents saw it after I put it up who live in an RV full time and wanted to know where I got it because they are constantly looking for space saving things. I love it so much I plan to purchase another one for the other side of my door because we are a family with a lot of shoes! I will say go with this brand because I loved the sturdiness I wanted to get one of a black color for my laundry room, it was roughly the same price, much smaller, couldn’t fit my husbands 13 size shoes, and not as nice. I plan to use it as shelves in my laundry room and not a shoe rack so it worked out but for a shoe rack it is no where comparable to this one. Look no further your space saving shoe rack is this one!!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Overall very pleased
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to store my son's shoes, which is good since my husband's shoes hang over the edge (as shown in pic). It's super easy to put together. My 4 y/o put it together with only a little help from me. It seems pretty sturdy for its use. At some point, I'll need to buy something to anchor it. I wish it came with a wall anchor but it's nbd. It was a tight squeeze to get the boards over the screws on the ends of the dowels but the dowels cover any cracks it causes so it's no harm done. I think the price fits the product. It comes with 6 little white stickers to cover the screw holes. You only need 3, which is a good thing because 3 stickers fell off the backing while in transit (as shown in pic) but, again, no harm done. The box it came in was pretty beat up. The materials were in the box without any packing material or protective coverings (which is better for the environment) so I'm surprised there wasn't any damage to the boards. Still, overall very pleased with the finished product. Super happy my son could assemble it. It really made him happy. He loves to help with projects like this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great space saver. Helpful hint for assembly...
reviews.reviewText: Some reviews mention the veneer getting cracked by the screws going through the holes. This happened to me on the very first piece, but the damage is hidden and I was able to finish the job without any more issues:You assemble by screwing 3 posts to a shelf, add a shelf, add 3 posts, shelf, posts, etc. to the top.When you add 3 posts, LEAVE THEM SLIGHTLY LOOSE so they have a little wobble/play in them. This allows them to move while you put on the next shelf. Then tighten the posts the last turn or so, add the next posts, again leaving them loose each time. This kept the shelves from catching on the screws and getting hurt, and the whole thing is nice and sturdy when complete. Hope this helps someone.That said, the end result is a great space-saving feature in the corner of a tight closet for me. The open-cornered design keeps it from blocking access to other shelves nearby and it turned a messy pile of shoes on my floor to a neat easy-access display. Just what I needed.
